# =============================================================================
# LumenWipe — Dokploy environment reference
# =============================================================================
# Dokploy splits config into three places. Paste each block into the matching
# section of the Dokploy UI. Do NOT paste this whole file into one box.
#
# Rule of thumb for this app:
#   - NEXT_PUBLIC_*  -> inlined into the client bundle by `next build`
#                       => Build-time Arguments (public, must exist at build).
#   - everything else (server-only secrets) -> read at request time
#                       => Environment Settings (runtime).
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# [ Build-time Arguments ]
# Dokploy UI: "Build-time Arguments". Passed as --build-arg and consumed by the
# ARG/ENV lines in the Dockerfile. Available ONLY at build. All values here end
# up in the browser bundle, so treat them as public (never put a secret key
# you need to keep private in a NEXT_PUBLIC_* var — it cannot be hidden).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Required
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_MAINNET=https://mainnet.stellar.validationcloud.io/v1/YOUR_KEY_HERE
NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_TESTNET=https://soroban-testnet.stellar.org
NEXT_PUBLIC_PATH_ROUTING_API_MAINNET=
NEXT_PUBLIC_PATH_ROUTING_API_TESTNET=

# Public mediator account keys (safe to expose; the SECRETs go in Environment
# Settings below). Needed for merges to exchanges that reject ACCOUNT_MERGE.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MEDIATOR_PUBLIC_MAINNET=
NEXT_PUBLIC_MEDIATOR_PUBLIC_TESTNET=

# Optional — RPC providers that need an auth header (QuickNode, DataHub, ...).
# NOTE: the value is exposed to the client because it is NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_HEADER_NAME_MAINNET=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_HEADER_VALUE_MAINNET=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_HEADER_NAME_TESTNET=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STELLAR_RPC_HEADER_VALUE_TESTNET=

# Optional — override StellarExpert API base (defaults in config/networks.ts).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SE_API_BASE_MAINNET=https://api.stellar.expert/explorer/public
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SE_API_BASE_TESTNET=https://api.stellar.expert/explorer/testnet

# Optional — Umami analytics. Omit to disable the script entirely.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# [ Build-time Secrets ]
# Dokploy UI: "Build-time Secrets" (mounted via BuildKit, never baked into a
# layer). Available ONLY at build.
#
# This project needs NONE: anything sensitive is read at runtime on the server,
# and anything needed at build is NEXT_PUBLIC_ (public). Leave this section
# empty. The Dockerfile shows the pattern if you ever add one (e.g. a private
# registry token consumed during install/build).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# (intentionally empty)


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# [ Environment Settings ]
# Dokploy UI: "Environment Settings". Available at container RUNTIME only.
# These are server-only secrets read by API routes — never prefixed with
# NEXT_PUBLIC_, so they never reach the browser.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Mediator secret keys (server-only counterpart to the public keys above).
# Required only for merges to exchanges that don't support ACCOUNT_MERGE.
MEDIATOR_SECRET_MAINNET=
MEDIATOR_SECRET_TESTNET=

# Vercel KV / Upstash-compatible Redis REST API. Required only for the merge
# stats counter and the playground session store; the app degrades without it.
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# Testnet playground (server-only). Generate via: bun scripts/setup-playground.ts
PLAYGROUND_ISSUER_SECRET_TESTNET=
PLAYGROUND_MM_SECRET_TESTNET=
PLAYGROUND_ENCRYPTION_KEY=